      {
        "id": 2043844,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-10-31T14:20:02.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Just heard that KP is harvesting Abtserde today! Photos of the fruit look magical: open, golden clusters with small berries.</p>\n<p>In reply to Claus, the 2004 is definitely the wine to drink now. We had a double magnum of the 04 Kirchspiel in September which was brilliant, and still very vibrant and youthful.</p>\n<p>For me, the Hubacker is the most exotic and brooding of Keller\u2019s 15 GGs, and it will need a bit of time in the cellar to unwind. It\u2019s a brilliant wine, as are all of KP\u2019s 15s. In fact, I have never tasted a better set of young wines from any producer, anywhere.</p>",
